Use the Observable.subscribe to manually invoke REST call/Observable


Use the .add to do what is essentially a finally block in Java
Can do something in dialog if REST call fails (e.g. don't reload the grid)

public quoteClicked() {
    let restCallFinishedSuccessfully: boolean = false;

    // Use subscribe to actually (manually) invoke the service, then use arrow function to get the result
    // of the Observable, then you can set this.quote = result
    this.quoteService.getQuote(this.myForm.controls.symbol.value).subscribe((aData: GetQuoteDetailsDTO) => {
      this.quote = aData;
      restCallFinishedSuccessfully = true;
    }).add(() => {
      // finally block
      // called whether REST call succeeds or not
      // can be used to 'stop spinner' if rest call fails

      // can check restCallFinishedSuccessfully
      if (!restCallFinishedSuccessfully) {
        // do some special logic
      }
    })
  }